   - Correct import: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next";`
   - Properly placed: `<SpeedInsights />` component added within the `<body>` tag
   - Follows Next.js 13.5+ App Router best practices

5. ✅ **Dependencies Installed**: Ran `npm install` to ensure all dependencies are properly installed.

6. ✅ **Build Verification**: Successfully ran `npm run build` - the project builds without errors.

7. ✅ **Linting**: Ran `npm run lint` - no linting errors found.

## Current Implementation

The Speed Insights implementation in `app/layout.tsx` follows the official documentation exactly:

```typescript
import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next";

export default function RootLayout({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return (
    <html lang="en">
      <body>
        <Navbar />
        <main>{children}</main>
        <Footer />
        <SpeedInsights />
      </body>
    </html>
  );
}
```

## Next Steps for Usage

To start collecting Speed Insights data:

1. Enable Speed Insights in the Vercel dashboard for your project
2. Deploy the application to Vercel (either via `vercel deploy` or by connecting the git repository)
3. After deployment and user visits, Speed Insights data will be available in the Vercel dashboard

